## 7. Phase 2 (Drive Later) Implementation Hook
Because we separated primary (critical path) and secondary (background) uploads, Phase 2 touches zero existing critical code. We just implement `driveService.ts`.

It plugs perfectly into the bottom of `photoController.ts`:

```typescript
// IN CONTROLLER (Phase 1):
export const uploadPhoto = async (req, res) => {
  // 1. Upload to Cloudinary (blocks)
  const cloudinaryUrl = await cloudinaryService.uploadImage(req.file.buffer);
  
  // 2. Save to Mongo (blocks)
  const photo = await Photo.create({
    cloudinaryUrl,
    placeSlug: req.body.placeSlug,
    /* ... uploader fields ... */
  });
  
  // 3. Complete Request immediately
  res.status(201).json(photo);

  // 4. FIRE AND FORGET - Background Job (Phase 2)
  driveService.backupToDriveInBackground(photo._id, req.file.buffer, req.body.placeSlug);
};
```

